article.headline: Tigers open with 25-2 run
article.linkText: Thanks for playing: LSU hammers Texas State
article.story:
BATON ROUGE, La. (AP) -- LSU head coach Pokey Chatman was
concerned her team might return from the Christmas break a little
lethargic. No worries.

Freshman Sylvia Fowles had 18 points and 11 rebounds in 16
minutes to lead No. 1 LSU to a 78-38 rout of Texas State on
Thursday night. She finished 9-of-12 from the field.

"We talked as a coaching staff about picking up where we left
off, and the kids came out from the very first possession and
established an energy," she said. "What really pleased me early
on was that we had an array of combinations and the energy was
still there."

The Tigers (12-0) opened with a 25-2 run in the first 9:30 and
held Texas State (3-8) to just 26-percent shooting.

LSU led by as many as 42 points in the second half. The Tigers
forced 25 Texas State turnovers and collected 16 steals. But LSU
went just 14-of-24 from the free-throw line.

"For the most part, we executed. We got to the free throw line
24 times, but we didn't quite finish a lot of them," Chatman said.
"However, we're making progress."

Temeka Johnson and Seimone Augustus added 13 points apiece for
LSU, which led 44-21 at halftime. Johnson also had six assists.

Tori Talbert had nine points for the Bobcats, who scored just 17
second-half points.

It was the first home game for LSU since beating North Texas at
the Pete Maravich Assembly Center on Nov. 30.
